My wife self-published because she already had an artist and everywhere that accepted her absolutely REFUSED to let her choose her own cover or internal art even though it had already been drawn before submission for the contracted interns at the publishing companies to review. (I swear, reviewing submissions at a publishing house must be no more than a few steps above &quot;cold-calling telemarketer&quot; for job satisfaction. You get to spend all of your time reading so much schlock, get shit pay, and probably burn out very shortly due to the sheer volume of pressure from all sides).<br />
<br />
Before she got pregnant, she spent every moment she could spare doing anything she could to market her stuff.<br />
<br />
It's more than a full time job and you got VERY little out of it until recently.<br />
<br />
Self-publishing as an internet industry has been around for almost 20 years and it's still coming into its own.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
