</div><a href="http://www.snopes.com/disney/wdco/daycare.asp" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://www.snopes.com/disney/wdco/daycare.asp</a>  yep they sue daycare centers too for painting images of their characters.  Disney is known for being downright rabid over copyright.   I bet if I made three circles with the right placement and posted them to this thread that the website would have a DMCA notice by morning.   Disney is likely more protective over any reference to their characters than Apple is over slide to unlock.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
